modules.description: Initializes an encoder and allows setting specific metadata fields such as title, artist, album, year, comment, track number, and genre. Operates on an encoder type to embed tags into audio files. Used to prepare audio files with custom metadata for playback systems that rely on ID3 tags.

Provides functions for encoding audio files to MP3 format, including initialization, configuration, and data processing. Works with raw audio data, MP3 bitstreams, and configuration parameters. Used to integrate MP3 encoding capabilities into OCaml applications requiring audio compression.

Encodes audio into MP3 format while embedding customizable ID3 metadata. Operates on an encoder type to set fields like title, artist, and genre. Supports adding track numbers, comments, and album information to audio files. Enables creation of tagged MP3s suitable for playback systems requiring structured metadata.
